# HomeOS server — environment template
# Copy to .env and fill in the REQUIRED values:   cp env.example .env
# Never commit .env (it's gitignored). Where each value comes from: apps/server/README.md.

# ── Required ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Any long random string. Paste the SAME value into Meta's webhook "Verify token".
VERIFY_TOKEN=

# Meta access token (used to send messages).
#   Demo 2:  the 24h temporary token from WhatsApp → API Setup.
#   Before dogfood:  swap for a non-expiring System User token.
WHATSAPP_TOKEN=

# The test number's "Phone number ID" (WhatsApp → API Setup) — NOT the phone number itself.
PHONE_NUMBER_ID=

# Allowlist gate: comma-separated E.164 family numbers — the SAME numbers you add as
# Meta recipients. Digits + country code (e.g. 972501234567); "+"/spaces are tolerated.
ALLOWLIST=

# Anthropic API key (console.anthropic.com → API keys). Read by @anthropic-ai/sdk.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Meta app secret (App Dashboard → Settings → Basic) — the HMAC key for X-Hub-Signature-256
# verification of the public POST /webhook. The server REFUSES TO BOOT without it (fail closed: the
# webhook is an unauthenticated write surface). For LOCAL dev — where you don't receive real signed
# webhooks — ANY non-empty string unblocks boot (e.g. local-dev-placeholder).
APP_SECRET=

# ── Optional (defaults shown; uncomment to override) ────────────────────────

# GRAPH_VERSION=v21.0
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6     # default (Haiku mis-resolves some Hebrew weekday idioms)
# DB_PATH=./data/homeos.db
# PORT=3000

# ── #225 Supabase Auth — the web board login gate ────────────────────────────
# Real per-user Google login via Supabase Auth REPLACED the old build-embedded READ/WRITE/MESSAGES bearer
# tokens. Set BOTH vars below to gate the read/write routes (GET /events, /messages, POST/PATCH /events,
# GET /oauth/google/status) on a logged-in + allowlisted user; leave BOTH unset to keep those routes
# DISABLED (503) — the app-only / dev default. The server verifies the session JWT LOCALLY against the
# cached JWKS (asymmetric ES256), so there's no per-request Supabase round-trip.
# Setup (Supabase project + the Google provider): docs/google-oauth-setup.md.
#
# Project URL (Supabase dashboard → Project Settings), e.g. https://<ref>.supabase.co:
# SUPABASE_URL=
# Comma-separated allowlist of Google accounts permitted to log in (the auth-side ALLOWLIST). A
# non-allowlisted account is rejected (403). Set alongside SUPABASE_URL; empty + URL-set fails fast at boot.
# ALLOWED_LOGIN_EMAILS=
#
# Supabase service_role key — SERVER-ONLY (dashboard → Project Settings → API). Reserved for future admin
# use; NOT read by the current session gate. 🔒 NEVER prefix it VITE_ / expose it to the web bundle.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# Web SPA build vars (#150/#225, same-origin serving) — read by Vite at BUILD time (pnpm --filter
# @homeos/web build), baked into the static bundle. The browser login needs the project URL + the
# PUBLISHABLE key (sb_publishable_…, safe in the bundle — NOT the service_role). See apps/web/env.example.
# Leave VITE_HOMEOS_API_BASE UNSET → empty = same origin (the server serves apps/web/dist; no CORS).
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=               # = SUPABASE_URL
# VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=   # the publishable key (sb_publishable_…)
# VITE_HOMEOS_API_BASE=            # leave empty for same-origin; set only for a split deploy

# (APP_SECRET moved to the REQUIRED section above — the server refuses to boot without it.)

# ── Offsite backup (#134, Cloudflare R2 — opt-in, ships DARK) ────────────────
# ALL-OR-NOTHING: set the whole R2 bundle (endpoint + bucket + both keys) or leave it ALL unset.
# Unset ⇒ the uploader is a no-op (the WAL-safe VACUUM-INTO snapshot still runs locally; nothing
# leaves the box). Set ⇒ every snapshot is streamed to a private EU R2 bucket. A half-filled bundle
# fails fast at boot. Setup steps: docs/r2-backup-setup.md.
# Privacy: the snapshot is the full DB — plaintext family data (event/forwarded text, phone numbers)
# goes to Cloudflare; only Google OAuth tokens are encrypted at rest. Keep the bucket private + the
# token least-privilege (object R/W/List/Delete on this one bucket). Restore = download the newest
# snapshot and point DB_PATH at it (a complete, consistent SQLite file).
# R2_ENDPOINT=https://<account>.eu.r2.cloudflarestorage.com   # account endpoint, no bucket
# R2_BUCKET=homeos-db
# R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# R2_PREFIX=default                # per-family object-key prefix (the single FAMILY_ID today)
# BACKUP_INTERVAL_HOURS=6          # snapshot cadence (bounds the RPO); default 6
# BACKUP_RETENTION_DAYS=14         # age out offsite snapshots older than this; default 14

# Open-thread TTL in MINUTES (#87/G24): how long a clarify/cancel/edit question stays answerable
# before it's swept, so a stale "do you mean A or B?" never resumes after a delay or a redeploy.
# Default 30 — long enough to survive a school pickup / meeting, tight enough to bound the held
# forwarded-text draft for privacy. A rate-limited sender is still allowed to CLOSE an open thread.
# CONVERSATION_TTL_MIN=30

# ── Google OAuth (#16, Phase 5 — opt-in, ships DARK) ─────────────────────────
# ALL-OR-NOTHING: set the whole bundle or leave it ALL unset. Unset ⇒ the feature is dark
# (routes 503, zero Google calls) — the forward-only red line holds. A HALF-filled bundle fails
# fast at boot. Setup steps + the visual test: docs/google-oauth-setup.md.
# Wired into config.ts (#60); the self-serve web flow + the SETUP_TOKEN/WEB_BASE_URL/ALLOWED_GOOGLE_EMAIL
# vars below are #10.
#
# From Google Cloud Console (see the setup runbook / your Perplexity walkthrough):
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
# Exact-match callback, character-for-character (OG14). Local dev value:
# GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/oauth/google/callback
#
# Generate locally (regenerate SEPARATE values for Railway/prod):
#   openssl rand -base64 32   → GOOGLE_TOKEN_ENC_KEY  (32-byte AES key; a CHANGED key fails loud at boot)
#   openssl rand -hex 32      → ADMIN_TOKEN           (gates /connect+/disconnect; distinct from SETUP_TOKEN)
# GOOGLE_TOKEN_ENC_KEY=
# ADMIN_TOKEN=
#
# ── Self-serve "Connect Google" (#10 — optional, within the bundle above) ─────
# Let a family connect Google themselves from the web Connections screen. Each OPTIONAL: absent ⇒
# admin-only mode (connect via the ADMIN_TOKEN curl path), unchanged. See the README "Connect Google" section.
#   openssl rand -base64 32   → SETUP_TOKEN  (≥32 bytes; MUST differ from ADMIN_TOKEN;
#                                              NEVER a VITE_* var — it's typed into the web dialog at runtime)
# SETUP_TOKEN=
# Absolute https:// URL on the in-code ALLOWED_WEB_ORIGINS allowlist; the callback bounces the browser to
# ${WEB_BASE_URL}/connections?status=<outcome>. Unset ⇒ the callback renders the static Hebrew page instead.
# WEB_BASE_URL=https://homeos-production-83a4.up.railway.app
# The single Google account the self-serve flow accepts (case-insensitive). Unset ⇒ unenforced.
# ALLOWED_GOOGLE_EMAIL=
#
# ── Sync tuning (optional — only consulted when the GOOGLE_* bundle is set) ───
# Cost/scope clamps for the "סנכרן מייל" (Gmail #17) and "סנכרן יומן" (Calendar #18) commands.
# All have safe defaults; uncomment only to tune.
#   Gmail:    GMAIL_MAX_MESSAGES=10  ·  GMAIL_QUERY_WINDOW=newer_than:7d  ·  GMAIL_ALLOWED_LABELS=
#   Calendar: CALENDAR_MAX_EVENTS=20  ·  CALENDAR_WINDOW_DAYS=30  ·  CALENDAR_ID=primary
# CALENDAR_MAX_EVENTS=20
# CALENDAR_WINDOW_DAYS=30
# CALENDAR_ID=primary
